## Real Django Request Cycle

### First Time Page Load

```text
User
 ↓
GET Request
 ↓
urls.py
 ↓
views.py
 ↓
Database (fetch records)
 ↓
home.html
 ↓
Browser
```

User existing data kaanunnu.

---

### Form Submit Cheyyumbol

```text
User
 ↓
POST Request
 ↓
urls.py
 ↓
views.py
 ↓
request.POST
 ↓
Model Object Create
 ↓
save()
 ↓
Database
```

Data database-il save aayi.

---

### Save Kazhinjal

Usually Django ingane cheyyum:

```text
Database
 ↓
redirect('/')
```

Reason:

* Duplicate form submission avoid cheyyan
* Refresh cheythal veendum save aakathirikkan

Ithine **PRG Pattern (Post → Redirect → Get)** enn parayum.

---

### Redirect Kazhinjal

```text
Browser
 ↓
GET Request
 ↓
urls.py
 ↓
views.py
 ↓
Database (fetch all data)
 ↓
Context
 ↓
home.html
 ↓
Browser
```

Ippol latest data display aakum.

---

## Interview-Level Understanding

Django-il data add cheyyunna correct flow:

```text
GET Request
 ↓
Display Form
 ↓
User Submit
 ↓
POST Request
 ↓
View
 ↓
Model
 ↓
Database Save
 ↓
Redirect
 ↓
GET Request
 ↓
Fetch Data
 ↓
Template Render
 ↓
Response
```

---

⚡ **Most important point:**

Data save cheytha sesham direct template render cheyyunnathinekkal Django projects-il **redirect → GET → render** pattern aanu common. Ithaan professional Django CRUD applications-il normally follow cheyyunnath.
